Launch a Virtual Machine and Execute Basic Shell Commands
➤ Step 1: Launch the Virtual Machine

• Start the Linux VM created in VirtualBox or any cloud platform.
• Wait for the Linux desktop or terminal login screen to appear.

➤ Step 2: Open the Terminal

• Open the Terminal from the applications menu
OR press Ctrl + Alt + T to open a new terminal window.

➤ Step 3: Execute Basic Shell Commands
➤ pwd (Print Working Directory)
pwd


• Shows the current directory path.

➤ ls (List Files and Folders)
ls


• Displays the files and directories inside the current location.

➤ cd (Change Directory)
cd /path/to/folder


• Moves into another directory.
Example:

cd /home

➤ mkdir (Make Directory)
mkdir myfolder


• Creates a new directory named myfolder.

➤ nano (Text Editor)
nano file.txt


• Opens a simple text editor to create or edit a file.

➤ top (Task Manager)
top


• Shows running processes, CPU usage, and memory usage in real time.
• Press q to exit.

➤ Step 4: Capture Outputs

• Take screenshots of:
– Terminal window
– Output of each command
– Created folders/files
– top command screen
